The paper describes the development of a real-time tracking algorithm that runs on a small UAV, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses image processing techniques such as cross-correlation and Kalman filtering, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system also involves autonomous decision-making and control, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the system, which could be evaluated using machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
